open-typer (4.0.0) bionic; urgency=high

  * Fixed memory leaks in language manager.
  * Added light blue theme.
  * Added an option to disable update checks on Windows.
  * Moved Class Monitor server to main application.
  * Open-Typer Class Monitor has been deprecated.
  * Added an option to disable mistake correction (the exercise is validated after it ends).
  * Added an option to hide exercise text.
  * Fixed exercise line length resetting after reloading a custom exercise.
  * Added validated text export.
  * Added menu bar to main window.
  * Fixed text resetting after opening options.
  * Removed page title from printed custom exercises.
  * Fixed mistakes at line end.
  * Fixed scrolling of mistake markers.
  * Fixed multiple mistakes in the same position.
  * Added a second server mode without any accounts (static IP addresses required).
  * Added typing test feature.
  * Switched to websocket.
  * Added window state saving.
  * Fixed inaccurate time in timed exercises.
  * Added mistakes (input text instead of the correct text) to exercise text preview.
  * Fixed calculation of gross and net hits.
  * Changed executable name to open-typer.
  * Created a PPA for Ubuntu (currently supports 18.04, 20.04 and 22.04).
  * Added support for i386, armhf and arm64 architectures (only in Ubuntu PPA).

 -- adazem009 <adazem.009.games@gmail.com>  Mon, 04 Jul 2022 10:55:02 +0200

